55 He was not yet very far from his rising,
56 when he began to make the earth feel
57 some comfort from his great virtue;

58 for such a lady, while still a youth, he went to war
59 against his father, to whom, as to death,
60 no one unlocks the door of pleasure;

61 and before his spiritual court
62 and coram patre he united himself to her;
63 then day by day he loved her more strongly.

64 This one, deprived of her first husband,
65 for more than thirteen hundred years, scorned and obscure,
66 remained without a suitor until this one;

67 nor did it avail that he found her safe
68 with Amiclates, at the sound of his voice,
69 he who made the whole world tremble;

76 Their harmony and their joyful countenances,
77 love and wonder and sweet gazes
78 made them a cause of holy thoughts;

88 Nor did the lowliness of his father's heart weigh down his brow,
89 for being the son of Pietro Bernardone,
90 nor for seeming wondrously despised;

112 to his brothers, as to rightful heirs,
113 he commended his most dear lady,
114 and commanded that they should love her faithfully;

118 Now consider what manner of man he was who was worthy
119 to be a colleague in keeping the bark
120 of Peter on the high seas by the straight course;

121 and this was our patriarch;
122 therefore you can discern that whoever follows him, as he commands,
123 carries a good cargo.

124 But his flock has become greedy for new food,
125 so that it cannot be
